Morgan DOS SANTOS is currently General Manager and Chief Scientific Officer of LabSkin Creations, a biotech company specialized in advanced tissue engineering and dedicated to the testing of cosmetics and pharmaceutical products on in vitro skin models. 

With a PhD in molecular and Cellular biology from Lyon University, France, Morgan has been developing for the past 18 years a high expertise in skin tissue engineering and 3D bioprinting. Originally trained in Edouard Herriot Hospital, one of the largest burn repair centre in Europe, he then moved to the cosmetics industry in which he actively contributed to the development of disruptive innovations in the field of skin bioengineering and skin care actives for dermatological and cosmetics applications.
After 7 years in China, working on skin fundamental research to transform disruptive science into innovation and new cosmetics product adapted to Asian consumers, he co-founded 2 biotech startup companies in the field of personal care testing and regenerative medicine, LabSkin Creations and HealShape. 

Morgan is author or co-author of many peer-reviewed journal papers and book chapters in the fields of tissue engineering and regenerative medicine, and he is also the co-inventor of PCT patents in bioprinting, epigenetics and active ingredients.

shortBio:
I am here to support women who want to take control of their sexual and reproductive health and their allies. With hundreds of conversations with people navigating complex sexual and reproductive health journeys, I've seen firsthand the barriers and stigmas that can prevent women from accessing the care they need. 

That's why I co-founded Ninti - to break down those barriers and provide women with the resources and support they need to make informed decisions about their health.

At Ninti, we believe that everyone deserves access to high-quality, evidence-based healthcare. That's why we've built a platform employers can offer with 3 core pillars: 

- evidence-based content to empower employees in navigating their health journey with confidence, from preconception to menopause and beyond.
- care with a variety of health and care professionals
- community to lean on, through events and circles

Our team and advisors are made up of experienced healthcare professionals, technologists, and entrepreneurs who are dedicated to driving innovation and making a difference in women's lives. 

We're backed by advisors who share our vision for a more empowered and healthy future for women. 

Join us in our mission to transform women's healthcare - one woman at a time. 
Reach out: hello@ninti.io

Dr. Wahid Awad, Ph.D., EMBA
Founder & CEO, Rosetta Omics

Dr. Wahid Awad is the Founder and CEO of Rosetta Omics, an innovative deeptech healthcare startup incubated at Agoranov. Rosetta Omics is on a mission to unlock the road to precision medicine by integrating spatial multiomics and AI, starting with oncology.

With an extensive international background, Dr. Awad has lived in Egypt, the Netherlands, the United States, and France, and has studied in 13 countries across five continents. His ability to navigate complex scientific and business landscapes is driven by an innovative problem-solving mindset.

Dr. Awad holds a bachelor‚Äôs degree from Egypt, a master‚Äôs degree from the Netherlands, a Ph.D. from the United States, and a postdoctoral fellowship from France. He later pursued an Executive MBA at ESCP Business School, completing the program across nine countries.

Before founding Rosetta Omics, Dr. Awad established Awad & Co., a life sciences-focused management consulting firm. He then served as Chief Business Officer and Board Member at CILcare, a French-American biotech and CRO with operations in Paris, Boston, Montpellier, and Copenhagen. During his tenure at CILcare, he spearheaded an in-residence entrepreneurship project, DiagOtology, which focused on auditory biomarkers and was designed to be spun out as an independent company.

Beyond his leadership in biotech, Dr. Awad plays an active role in the health innovation ecosystem. He is an elected board member of:

Paris Saclay Cancer Cluster Connect
Medicen Paris Region
ESCP Business School Alumni Association
American University Club in France

Passionate about education and mentorship, he serves as a visiting professor at multiple business schools and universities in France. Prior to focusing on Rosetta Omics, he held a tenure-track Assistant Professor position at Cairo University.

Dr. Awad‚Äôs contributions to science, innovation, and leadership have earned him over 20 awards, fellowships, and honors across four countries. He was also nominated as a Young Global Leader by the World Economic Forum, recognizing his impact in life sciences and healthcare.

His journey in cancer research is deeply personal‚Äîhaving lost his father to cancer, he has made it his life‚Äôs mission to revolutionize cancer care. In his free time, he runs to support cancer patients, actively fundraising for Gustave Roussy, Europe‚Äôs largest cancer hospital.

As an expert in the renewable energy domain, I bring over a decade of experience driving sustainable growth and innovation. A graduate of one of France's leading engineering schools specializing in new technologies, my passion for IT and telecom was solidified through my tenure at Huawei Technologies France. I began my career driving market breakthroughs and developing new business markets, focusing on the African and European telecommunication sectors. During my first six years, I gained valuable experience in PM and MS environments, and honed my skills in project management, process analysis, and improvement. My efforts consistently contributed to significant financial gains for Huawei France.

In 2013, I transitioned to the solar industry to develop Huawei's service platform in Europe and spearhead sales in France and the Benelux region. Over the next decade, I led the business to remarkable success, achieving sustainable growth and enhancing team structure and capabilities. Under my leadership, Huawei secured a leading position in the French market for utility, C&I, and residential business, capturing over 30% market share and recruiting a talented team of over 60 members from scratch.

Since 2020, I have served as the Managing Director of the France Digital Power department, where I established and grew sales and technical teams for solar, datacenter, and EV charger. Additionally, I have been a board member of Huawei France Technologies. Over the past three years, my team and I have driven sustainable business growth and delivered over 10 GW of renewable energy projects worldwide, achieving high customer satisfaction.

In addition to my role at Huawei, I have been actively involved in industry associations and networks. I serve as the VP of R&D and Industry of SER-SOLER, the solar PV commission at the French Renewable Energy Association, and as a board member of Synergie Renouvelable, a charity supporting renewable energy initiatives in Europe, Africa, and Latin America. I also founded VinaSolar, a French wine club dedicated to the energy transition. As a keynote speaker and guest lecturer at various events and institutions, I share my expertise and insights with the broader community.

Earlier in my career at Huawei, I was a member of the Social and Economic Committee (CSE), where I contributed to enhancing employee welfare and organizational efficiency.

I am deeply committed to the renewable industry and believe in fostering innovation, trust, respect, professionalism, teamwork, and dedication to drive operational excellence across organizations.
